Subject:Re: [EVDL] EVLN: Don't 'Jaws of Life' the orange cables
The title is quite misleading, because Jaws of Life are
typically used to open doors and cut pillars to lift the
roof off if a door is stuck or a better access is needed
to a wounded/entrapped passenger.
I have never seen them cut through frame members, which
is typically where conduits for high voltage (as well as
brake lines, fuel lines and so on) always run.

The warning about quiet operation and the inability to
see or hear if the car is ready to "go" is a very valid one.

Cor van de Water
Chief Scientist
Proxim Wireless Corporation http://www.proxim.com
