Subject: Re: [EVDL] EVLN: Don't 'Jaws of Life' the orange cables

I recommend that all high voltage cable runs be in flexible
underground-rated conduit.  This stuff is extremely tough, but also
flexible and yielding in a crash.  Batteries should be heavily secured.
I
am not talking about 1/4" all-thread.  I am suggesting 1/2" or 5/8"
all-thread/bolts.  Do the math on the weight of the battery pack under
10
G's accelleration.  Safety is #1.  All it takes is ONE sloppy EV to give
us
all a bad name.

Cheers,
Marcus

